children.subject: How would waitlist/enrollment work for non-CS students?
Calcentral is still asking for a permission number when I try to add/swap into 186. Is this because there is technically still a conflict, or do we need a permission number?

history.content:
As a few of you have noticed, there has been some movement in CS 186 and Prof. Hellerstein is now listed as the instructor of record.

Please be aware that this class is still CLOSED for enrollment. We do this by marking the class as requiring Instructor or Department Consent. PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT PROF HELLERSTEIN about enrolling in the class.

In addition to finding an instructor, we need to complete some other tasks before we can open the class for enrollment. We do not anticipate completing these tasks before Phase 1 ends, so we will open CS 186 for enrollment at the beginning of Phase 2.

Look for additional information about CS 186 sometime next week.
